    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is attributable to the standardized single-condition nature of ASTM F1717 and is consistent with accepted FDA practice for this device class. The overall evidence package provides sufficient credibility at Medium assurance level to support the regulatory submission claim that the FEA framework accurately predicts compression-bending performance of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds.",
